\section{Synchrotron}
A synchrotron (see Fig.~\ref{fig:synchrotron}) is a circular accelerator where the nominal particle trajectory is kept at a
constant physical radius by variation of both the magnetic field and the radio frequency, in order to follow the energy variation.
In this way, the aperture of the vacuum chamber and the magnets can be kept small.

